  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Cut the <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into chips, then add them to a baking tray with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong>, <strong>half</strong> the <strong>smoked paprika </strong>(you'll use the rest later!)<strong> </strong>and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and put the tray in the oven for 20-25 min or until the chips are golden and crisp – these are your <strong>paprika chips</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-copy-4-1657628036176-x200.jpg",
